The paper proposes a system for autonomous driving that involves planning and prediction of other vehicles' trajectories and goals. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with autonomous systems. The system also involves machine learning techniques such as rational inverse planning and Monte Carlo Tree Search, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for perception tasks. Finally, the system is designed to operate in a control system (cs.SY) context, as it involves generating optimal plans for the ego vehicle.
